A person who participates in the illegal drug market at a level one, two, three, or four offense shall be considered to have participated in the following illegal drug market target communities:



	(1)	For a level one offense, the area identified by the tax map section in which the defendants place of participation is situated;
	(2)	For a level two offense, the area identified by the tax map zone in which the defendants place of participation is situated;
	(3)	For a level three offense, the county; provided that in the case of Maui and Kauai counties, the target community shall be any island in the respective county; and



	(4)	For a level four offense, the entire State. [L 2004, c 44, pt of §13]
